{"TopicId":217174,"ForumId":129,"TopicTitle":"Docking port alignment","CreatedByName":"EmanonP","CreatedById":60201,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-13T11:14:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"EmanonP","CreatedById":60201,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-13T11:14:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould LOVE to see this mod introduced for KSP2.\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0I happily admit I suck at eyeball docking, and that mod in KSP1 was awesome.\u00A0 \u00A0(Navyfish I do believe).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stephensmat","CreatedById":200752,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-14T06:23:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy main complaint about KSP2 is that I seem to have \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/217059-version-0120-22258-cannot-choose-another-craft-as-target/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Elucked into a bug where I can\u0027t target nearby ships for docking\u003C/a\u003E. A mod that lets me pick docking ports would be quite appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LuxStice","CreatedById":149802,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-22T13:20:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll try to bring this, not a priority tho\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"schlosrat","CreatedById":141963,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-25T02:56:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224283152\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217174\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221684045411\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022200752\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022stephensmat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/14/2023 at 2:23 AM, stephensmat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy main complaint about KSP2 is that I seem to have \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/217059-version-0120-22258-cannot-choose-another-craft-as-target/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Elucked into a bug where I can\u0027t target nearby ships for docking\u003C/a\u003E. A mod that lets me pick docking ports would be quite appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood news for you! Flight Plan already does this! You can use Flight Plan to select either celestial or vessel targets. Not only that, but if your target is another vessel and it\u2019s relatively near by (within 3km) then you\u2019ll have the option \u00A0of targeting specific docking ports on the target vessel!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022141963\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed232797500\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/216393-flight-plan/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}